Exercise done in SQLite Online IDE:

(Docs -> https://www.w3schools.com/sql/)

>>> Reading ALL the data from a table:
SELECT * FROM 'products';

>>> Reading data from a specific COLUMN:
SELECT name, price FROM 'products';

>>> Reading data from a specific ROW (Use WHERE):
SELECT * FROM 'products' WHERE id=1;

>>> Reading data from a ROW using a specific column name:
SELECT name FROM 'products' WHERE id=1;